      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sewall's_Point%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town sits on a peninsula bordered by the St. Lucie River to the south and west and the Indian River Lagoon to the east.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16,
        17,
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sewall's_Point%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Sewall's Point was named after Henry Edwin Sewall, a 19th‑century landowner who helped develop the area.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sewall's_Point%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The town’s tropical savanna climate (Köppen Aw) gives it weather similar to the Caribbean.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20,
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sewall's_Point%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
